{"id":35948,"title":"Repair of ventricular septal defect with Eisenmenger syndrome after bosentan treatment.","abstract":"We report a patient with ventricular septal defect (VSD) and Eisenmenger syndrome. The patient was treated with bosentan for 12 weeks, with a decrease in pulmonary vascular resistance index (PRVi) from 18.84 to 9.63 Wood unit (WU)?m2 , and underwent successful corrective repair of the VSD after 12 weeks of bosentan therapy.","date":"2014-04-25","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24612361","annotations":[{"name":"Ventricular septal defect","weight":0.893958,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ventricular_septal_defect"},{"name":"Congenital heart defect","weight":0.771483,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congenital_heart_defect"},{"name":"Ventricle (heart)","weight":0.735569,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ventricle_(heart)"},{"name":"Lung","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lung"},{"name":"Blood vessel","weight":0.644599,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_vessel"},{"name":"Eisenmenger's syndrome","weight":0.526543,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eisenmenger's_syndrome"},{"name":"Congenital disorder","weight":0.433618,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congenital_disorder"},{"name":"Syndrome","weight":0.371614,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syndrome"},{"name":"Vascular resistance","weight":0.35861,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vascular_resistance"},{"name":"Interventricular septum","weight":0.21349,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interventricular_septum"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.110873,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Bosentan","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bosentan"},{"name":"Septum